<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-10-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Severe Respiratory Illness Outbreak Associated with Human Coronavirus NL63 in a Long-Term Care Facility</TITLE><BODY>We describe an outbreak of severe respiratory illness associated with human coronavirus NL63 in a long-term care facility in Louisiana in November 2017. Six of 20 case-patients were hospitalized with pneumonia, and 3 of 20 died. Clinicians should consider human coronavirus NL63 for patients in similar settings with respiratory disease.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>